Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo Many people were feared dead in a road accident that occurred at Igbelajewa Village, along the Ilesha-Akure Expressway, on Monday, when a truck carrying diesel lost control, spilt its content and caught fire. About seven vehicles, including an 18-passenger commercial bus were reportedly burnt. Spokesperson for Osun Command of Nigeria Police Force, Yemisi Opalola, confirmed the accident, saying the number of the victims could not be ascertained yet. Details laterâ€¦